<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <pre class="highlight"><code>
$request = new \Zend\Http\Request;
$request-&gt;setMethod('post');
echo $request-&gt;getMethod(); // output is lowercase 'post'
</code></pre>

<p>For web servers that adhere strictly to the HTTP standard (like nginx), this will cause a 400/Unknown method error. Zend\Http\Request should automatically convert the string passed to setMethod() to uppercase.</p>

<p>Additionally, Zend\Http\Client::setMethod() should utilize the "uppercased" method returned after setting the method in the request when checking the method type to see if calling setEncType is necessary.</p>

